<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-05-15T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-05-15T04:00:00-05:00" n="142" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d142">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/4433: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-15T10:00:00+01:00">May 15, 1936—10
                                    a.m.</date><lb/>[Received May 16—8:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>173. The Secretariat issued last evening a communication from the
                                Chilean representative<note n="40" xml:id="d142fn40">League of
                                    Nations, <hi rend="italic">Official Journal</hi>, Special
                                    Supplement No. 150, p. 338.</note> in which it is stated, “My
                                Government is of the opinion that in view of the recent events which
                                have put an end to the war between Ethiopia and Italy, it would be
                                proper to discontinue the economic, financial and other measures
                                decided upon in connection with this conflict”.</p>
                            <p>In view of this communication being in terms of a proposal it is not
                                known here whether Chile has actually discontinued the sanctions
                                measures.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>